On [[3 July]] [[1961]], [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] wrote '''[[Letters not published in The Letters of J.R.R. Tolkien|a letter]] to Mr. Gilmore'''. The one-page typed and signed letter, in which Tolkien explains why there cannot be [[The New Shadow|a sequel]] to ''[[The Lord of the Rings]]'', was put up for auction in early 2019 at Bonhams.<ref>{{webcite|author=|articleurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20190311192641/https://www.bonhams.com/auctions/25354/lot/252/|articlename=TOLKIEN (J.R.R.) Typed letter signed ("J.R.R. Tolkien"), to Mrs Gilmore, explaining why there cannot be a sequel to The Lord of the Rings|dated=|website=[https://www.bonhams.com Bonhams]|accessed=16 March 2019}}</ref>
